        <name xml:lang="en">hydrochloric acid, without water, in 30% solution state</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">As there was no data available for the production of dimethyl malonate, the values for the consumption of the raw materials are calculated with an assumed yield of 95 % per step (Frischknecht et al. 2007). Hydrochloric acid and sodium hydroxide are calculated with a yield of 95% if they are used as raw material, and with a yield of 100% if they are used for neutralization of remaining acid or base. The remaining sodium hydroxide from the first step is considered to be neutralized with hydrogen chloride. In the second step the remaining hydrochloric acid is neutralized with sodium hydroxide.</comment>
